The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Cops foil robbery attempt
                                                                                                               Cops foil robbery attempt
          OUR CORRESPONDENT                               
	Bhubaneswar, June 4: Police chased and arrested three members of a gang, nipping a robbery bid in the bud at Patia Square on the outskirts of the city last night. Five live bombs were found on them.         
	Around 9pm last night, three police vans chased the gang of five criminals on motorbikes and opened fire.        
	The men, belonging to the gang of Jatia of Cuttack, were there to execute a large operation.         
	But the police managed to foil their attempts.         
	Three members of the gang have been arrested and five live bombs, a loaded revolver and sharp weapons were recovered from the spot.        
	The heavy exchange of fire left two injured  policeman Sudarshan Mohanty from Infocity police station and gang member Rajiv Patnaik.         
	Mohanty sustained a bullet injury and was rushed to the Capital Hospital and later shifted to Ayush Hospital in the city.         
	His condition is stable now. Patnaik was taken to SCB Medical College and Hospital, Cuttack, with a bullet lodged in his left thigh.         
	We had definite information about the gangs movement, police commissioner Bijay Sharma said. But key accused Jatia and two others managed to flee.         
	He said the five men on two bikes opened fire at the sight of the policemen.         
	The policemen returned fire and managed to capture two criminals while the others headed towards Cuttack, along Barang Road.         
	The police gave them a hot chase and another exchange of fire followed.                                                                                                                                                                            
